tment of the movie [[Um Funeral \u00e0 Chuva]] [2010] (''Funeral in the rain'')<ref>[http://diario.iol.pt/cinema/funeral-a-chuva-telmo-martins-covilha/1110738-4059.html (in Portuguese) IOL Di\u00e1rio - \u00abUm Funeral \u00e0 Chuva\u00bb foi feito sem dinheiro, mas \u00abpodia custar um milh\u00e3o de euros\u00bb] (1 February 2010)</ref> - by Portuguese film maker [[Telmo Martins]] and edited by [[Jos\u00e9 Nascimento (film director)|Jos\u00e9 Nascimento]]  - creating the lead soundtrack and sound design.<ref>[http://www.loudmagazine.net/blog/2009_12_01_archive.html (in Portuguese) Revista Loud - arquivo not\u00edcias] (9 December 2009)</ref>\n\n==Music==\nAs a musician, the multi-instrumentist is part of several music acts such as [[Ghost Orchid (band)|Ghost Orchid]] and ([[Aura (band)|arua]]). While Ghost Orchid is a more song-oriented atmospheric post rock project, (aura) is a more experimental project going through antagonistic and diversified musical styles and fusing the music itself with lots of sound design and cinematic elements.<ref>[http://a-trompa.net/ca/netlabels/netlabelsinvisible-landscape-aura (in Portuguese) A Trompa - (aura) - invisible landscape] (2 February 2009)</ref> (aura)'s debut album [[invisible landscape]] is an imaginary soundtrack inspired on the photographic work of [[Jos\u00e9 Ramos (photographer)|Jos\u00e9 Ramos]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fernandes, Andre}}\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n<!-- The nomination page for this article already existed when this tag was added.  If this was because the article had been nominated for deletion before, and you wish to renominate it, please replace \"page=Andr\u00e9 Fernandes\" with \"page=Andr\u00e9 Fernandes (2nd nomination)\" below before proceeding with the nomination.\n-->{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Andr\u00e9 Fernandes|timestamp=20200425174100|year=2020|month=April|day=25|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Andr\u00e9 Fernandes|date=25 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Andr\u00e9 F. Fernandes\n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name       = Andr\u00e9 Fernandes\n| alias            = \n| birth_place      = [[Oporto]], Portugal\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = \n| occupation       = Musician, composer, producer\n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = <!-- YYYY\u2013YYYY (or \u2013present) -->\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n}}\n'''Andr\u00e9 F. Fernandes''' is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] musician, composer and producer who creates [[film score]]s and original music for television and movies.\n\n==Film and television==\nHe produced original music for several mainstream advertising campaigns and has developed music and sound for several TV shows. In cinema, he has directed both the sound and music department of the movie [[Um Funeral \u00e0 Chuva]] [2010] (''Funeral in the rain'')<ref>[http://diario.iol.pt/cinema/funeral-a-chuva-telmo-martins-covilha/1110738-4059.html (in Portuguese) IOL Di\u00e1rio - \u00abUm Funeral \u00e0 Chuva\u00bb foi feito sem dinheiro, mas \u00abpodia custar um milh\u00e3o de euros\u00bb] (1 February 2010)</ref> - by Portuguese film maker [[Telmo Martins]] and edited by [[Jos\u00e9 Nascimento (film director)|Jos\u00e9 Nascimento]]  - creating the lead soundtrack and sound design.<ref>[http://www.loudmagazine.net/blog/2009_12_01_archive.html (in Portuguese) Revista Loud - arquivo not\u00edcias] (9 December 2009)</ref>\n\n==Music==\nAs a musician, the multi-instrumentist is part of several music acts such as [[Ghost Orchid (band)|Ghost Orchid]] and ([[Aura (band)|arua]]). While Ghost Orchid is a more song-oriented atmospheric post rock project, (aura) is a more experimental project going through antagonistic and diversified musical styles and fusing the music itself with lots of sound design and cinematic elements.<ref>[http://a-trompa.net/ca/netlabels/netlabelsinvisible-landscape-aura (in Portuguese) A Trompa - (aura) - invisible landscape] (2 February 2009)</ref> (aura)'s debut album [[invisible landscape]] is an imaginary soundtrack inspired on the photographic work of [[Jos\u00e9 Ramos (photographer)|Jos\u00e9 Ramos]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fernandes, Andre}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added {{Uncategorized}} tag (UsingTwinkle)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Fernandes"}
